{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "guidegroom::2.0", "icon": "FUR/shears", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Guide Groom"], "extent": [81, 97]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Interactively creates and modifies guide curves."], "extent": [97, 154]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node is a tool for creating guide curves for any type of groom."], "extent": [154, 224]}, {"level": 2, "id": "groomradial", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Grooming radial menu"], "extent": [224, 265], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When using the Guide Groom SOP, make sure to switch to the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Grooming"]}, " radial menu from the top menu bar. This menu lets you quickly switch tools options in the viewport, and is the recommended workflow when using this node."], "extent": [265, 497]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/fur/guidegroom_radialmenu.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [497, 548]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["After switching to the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Grooming"]}, " radial, you can open it by pressing ", {"keys": ["C"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, ". This brings up a menu that contains all the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tool"]}, " options for the Guide Groom SOP, and reflects the options available in the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tool"]}, " dropdown parameter on the node. It\u2019s a quick way to switch between the options on this node."], "extent": [548, 862]}, {"type": "col_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [862, 872], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/fur/guidegroom_radialmenu_top.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [872, 930]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [930, 940], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/fur/guidegroom_radialmenu_submenu.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [940, 1003]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For example, if you hover your mouse over ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Create & Move"]}, ", you will see the 4 options available for creating and moving hair. You can either choose one, or navigate back to the previous level by hovering your mouse over the double arrows."], "extent": [1003, 1249]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Each ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tool"]}, " has a ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Tool Options"]}, " menu that is unique to that mode. For example, the tool options available in ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Draw"]}, " mode are different than the ones available in ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Plant"]}, " mode."], "extent": [1249, 1439]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tools"], "extent": [1439, 1451], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This section documents tools available in Guide Groom\u2019s viewport state via the radial menu described above."], "extent": [1451, 1561]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create & Move"], "extent": [1561, 1583], "body": [{"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Draw"], "extent": [1583, 1599], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Draw individual hair curves."], "extent": [1599, 1633]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click and drag on the character\u2019s skin and draw out from it to create a hair curve."], "extent": [1633, 1722]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Various options are available to modify the drawing behavior. You can draw the entire hair on the character\u2019s skin by enabling ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Draw on Skin"]}, "."], "extent": [1722, 1872]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Draw parting lines by changing ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Curve Type"]}, " to."], "extent": [1872, 1927]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of curve segments created is governed by the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Segment Mode"]}, " parameter. Set this to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Fixed"]}, " to create hairs with a predefined number of segments. Set it to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Adaptive"]}, " in order to create more segments for longer curves."], "extent": [1927, 2163]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Plant"], "extent": [2163, 2179], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click on the characters skin to create a hair at that point."], "extent": [2179, 2245]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["To create many hairs, switch to ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scatter Mode"]}, " and set the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Radius"]}, " and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Density"]}, " parameters. ", {"keys": ["MMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " Deletes curves under the brush."], "extent": [2245, 2390]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["To match the shape of surrounding hairs, enable ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Interpolate Guides"]}, ". With this disabled (or when there are no hairs), the new hair will simply stick out straight from the surface. Length is then controlled by the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Default Length"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [2390, 2641]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "ui", "text": ["Interpolate Relative to Skin"]}, " will interpolate surrounding hairs but rotate the created hair to match the clicked point\u2019s skin curvature."], "extent": [2641, 2787]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Move"], "extent": [2787, 2802], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Move points around the character skin."], "extent": [2802, 2846]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["To rotate points with the curvature of the skin, enable ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Rotate with Skin"]}], "extent": [2846, 2928]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Relax"], "extent": [2928, 2944], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Evens out spacing between hairs. You can control the amount of space using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Density"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [2944, 3051]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Delete"], "extent": [3051, 3068], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Deletes hair under the brush."], "extent": [3068, 3104]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cull"], "extent": [3104, 3119], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Deletes hair until the density matches the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Density"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [3119, 3191]}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sculpt"], "extent": [3191, 3206], "body": [{"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Smooth"], "extent": [3206, 3224], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Smooths the shape of curves, removing any high frequency detail."], "extent": [3224, 3294]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The higher the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Smoothness"]}, " parameter, the more details are smoothed out."], "extent": [3294, 3375]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clump"], "extent": [3375, 3391], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clumps together any curves under the cursor. You can do this for the entire curve at once or in a more controlled way using ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Per Point"]}, "."], "extent": [3391, 3536]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"keys": ["MMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " Separates the curves."], "extent": [3536, 3571]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sculpt"], "extent": [3571, 3588], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sculpt curves by clicking and dragging."], "extent": [3588, 3634]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sculpt with Physics"], "extent": [3634, 3664], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Brush hair while simulating using Vellum physics."], "extent": [3664, 3720]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Live Simulation"]}, " to run the simulation at all times, even while not actively brushing."], "extent": [3720, 3822]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Settle Mode"]}, " to drop hair under gravity."], "extent": [3822, 3875]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Damped Mode"]}, " to get the effects of physics simulation, with hair floating weightlessly."], "extent": [3875, 3975]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Blur"], "extent": [3975, 3990], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Blends (averages) the shapes of hair under the brush."], "extent": [3990, 4050]}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Brush & Edit"], "extent": [4050, 4071], "body": [{"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Deintersect"], "extent": [4071, 4094], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Attempts to fix skin intersections, where part of the hair dives under the character\u2019s skin."], "extent": [4094, 4193]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Transform Handle"], "extent": [4193, 4220], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use this tool to move curves or individual points using a transform handle."], "extent": [4220, 4302]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "ui", "text": ["Soft Transform"]}, " softly transforms the entire curve or part of it, depending on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Soft Transform Mode"]}, "."], "extent": [4302, 4418]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"keys": ["Shift"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " & Drag on the handle to clone curves. You can also clone end points to extend the curve."], "extent": [4418, 4522]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [4522, 4531], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["After doing this, you may use ", {"keys": ["Shift+D"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to redistribute points evenly along the curve. Or use ", {"keys": ["Shift+R"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to resample to a different segment count."], "extent": [4531, 4690]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Brush"], "extent": [4690, 4706], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Brushes hair, rotating from the root."], "extent": [4706, 4750]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can also bend hairs by increasing the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Bend"]}, " parameter. The shape of the bend is the controlled by the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Bend Falloff"]}, "."], "extent": [4750, 4882]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Adjust Length"], "extent": [4882, 4906], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["In ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Add / Subtract Mode"]}, ", ", {"keys": ["LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to increase length, ", {"keys": ["MMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " to decrease."], "extent": [4906, 4989]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "ui", "text": ["Set Mode"]}, " adjusts length until it matches the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Length"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [4989, 5065]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["With the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Scale Method"]}, ", the hair shape simply scales uniformly."], "extent": [5065, 5137]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["With the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Cut / Extend Method"]}, ", hairs are extended or trimmed at the tip."], "extent": [5137, 5218]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Lift"], "extent": [5218, 5233], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Changes the orientation of hairs relative to the skin plane."], "extent": [5233, 5300]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["In ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Add / Subtract Mode"]}, ", ", {"keys": ["LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " raises and ", {"keys": ["MMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " lowers."], "extent": [5300, 5368]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["In ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Set Mode"]}, ", hair is rotated until the angle matches the set ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Angle"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [5368, 5459]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Straighten"], "extent": [5459, 5480], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Straightens the entire hair shape into a straight line, keeping the original length."], "extent": [5480, 5571]}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group & Mask"], "extent": [5571, 5592], "body": [{"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Paint Group Tool"], "extent": [5592, 5620], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["By default, this paints the currently set ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Active Name"]}, " onto curves, but you can also change parameters under the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Groups"]}, " header to add brushed curves to a group instead."], "extent": [5620, 5802]}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Paint Mask Tool"], "extent": [5802, 5828], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Paint a mask attribute. Other tools use this to limit their effects to the painted region. The mask can be painted per point by enabling ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Paint Points"]}, "."], "extent": [5828, 5989]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"keys": ["LMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " Adds to the mask, ", {"keys": ["MMB"], "type": "keys", "text": null}, " removes."], "extent": [5989, 6037]}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For more information, see the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/fur/groom", "type": "link", "text": ["Creating and styling guide hair with Guide Groom"], "fullpath": "/fur/groom"}, " page."], "extent": [6037, 6136]}]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [6136, 6148], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clear"], "extent": [6148, 6156], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clears all edits, which resets back to the unmodified input or no geometry at all if no input is connected."], "extent": [6172, 6285]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "clear"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [6285, 6292], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The currently selected elements to be groomed."], "extent": [6308, 6360]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "group"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group Type"], "extent": [6360, 6372], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The element type of the current selection."], "extent": [6392, 6440]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "grouptype"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Mask"], "extent": [6440, 6450], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reduces the effect of brushes and tools based on a painted mask. Use the Paint Mask tool to modify this mask."], "extent": [6468, 6583]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You\u2019ll also find mask related tools in the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#groomradial", "type": "link", "text": ["Grooming Radial Menu"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/guidegroom#groomradial", "fragment": "#groomradial"}], "extent": [6583, 6667]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "usemask"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tool"], "extent": [6667, 6673], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The currently selected tool. The most convenient way to switch between tools is by using the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#groomradial", "type": "link", "text": ["Grooming Radial Menu"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/guidegroom#groomradial", "fragment": "#groomradial"}, "."], "extent": [6688, 6823]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "tool"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Ray Bias"], "extent": [6823, 6833], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The thickness of the collision layer around the character\u2019s skin. The Guide Groom SOP prevents curves from passing through this outer layer while you edit them."], "extent": [6851, 7017]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ideal value would be something like 1/10th or 1/100th of the shortest segment length in a groom. Making it much larger would keep curve points at a large distance from the skin. Making it too small would make it easier for curves to end up inside the skin."], "extent": [7017, 7283]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "raybias"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Edit Selection as Clump"], "extent": [7283, 7308], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Brushing the selection will modify it as a whole, as if all selected curves were clumped together. This makes it easier to preserve the volume of existing clumps while sculpting."], "extent": [7329, 7513]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "strandmode"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Collide with Skin"], "extent": [7513, 7532], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Prevents guides from passing through the character\u2019s skin. It can be useful to turn this off in certain situations. For example, when guide are already stuck inside the skin and you want to move them back out."], "extent": [7558, 7773]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "collidewithskin"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Brush Options"], "extent": [7773, 7793], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Surface Brush"], "extent": [7793, 7809], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Brush on the character\u2019s surface. When this checkbox is turned off, the brush is in screen space. Most tools work either way, but for some tools such as ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Plant"]}, ", this is always enabled since it only makes sense to plant guides on the surface of the skin."], "extent": [7832, 8094]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "brushsurface"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Respect Parting Lines"], "extent": [8094, 8117], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When this checkbox is turned on, a brush will only affect guides on the cursor\u2019s side of a parting line. This only works when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Brush"]}, " is turned on, because the brushes' projected skin location is used to determine which side it is on."], "extent": [8143, 8393]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "usepartinglines"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Screen Radius"], "extent": [8393, 8408], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The brush radius in pixels, when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Brush"]}, " is turned off."], "extent": [8431, 8502]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "screenradius"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Object Radius"], "extent": [8502, 8517], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The brush radius in Houdini units, when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Brush"]}, " is turned on."], "extent": [8540, 8617]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "objectradius"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Strength"], "extent": [8617, 8627], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The strength of the brush effect."], "extent": [8646, 8685]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "strength"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Softness"], "extent": [8685, 8695], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The softness of the brush shape."], "extent": [8710, 8748]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "soft"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Spacing"], "extent": [8748, 8757], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When this is non-zero, the brush will be splatted at regular pixel intervals, regardless of how fast you move the cursor. This only works when ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Surface Brush"]}, " is turned off."], "extent": [8775, 8956]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "spacing"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Per Point"], "extent": [8956, 8967], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Apply operation per point rather than per curve."], "extent": [8967, 9021]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Maintain Length"], "extent": [9021, 9038], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount the the length of curves is preserved while brushing. Values lower than 1 allow you to modify curve lengths by brushing along the curve."], "extent": [9068, 9221]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "brushmaintainlength"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bend"], "extent": [9221, 9227], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Values over 0 cause curves to bend more as you brush them, rather than just rotating from the root."], "extent": [9247, 9352]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "brushbend"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bend Falloff"], "extent": [9352, 9366], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Higher values cause curves to bend more at the tip, lower values cause them to bend more easily at the root."], "extent": [9393, 9507]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "brushbendfalloff"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotate with Skin"], "extent": [9507, 9525], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Rotates curves with the skin curvature as you move them."], "extent": [9554, 9616]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "moverotatewithskin"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Constrain Length"], "extent": [9616, 9634], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Constrain the length of curve segments as you sculpt."], "extent": [9662, 9721]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sculptdoconstrain"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Lock Root"], "extent": [9721, 9732], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Locks the root in place as you sculpt."], "extent": [9757, 9801]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sculptlockroot"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Smoothness"], "extent": [9801, 9813], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "smoothtargetsmoothness"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mode"], "extent": [9846, 98